Story Loop — Step 1 of 6
Choose the input source for this loop:
**[1] Story file** — I already have a story markdown ready for dev (e.g. `implementation_artifacts/1-2-user-auth.md`) **[2] Jira issue** — Fetch a Jira ticket and generate a story from it **[3] Free-form prompt** — Describe the feature; I will generate the story **[4] Sprint next** — Take the next `ready-for-dev` story from {{sprint_status}}

Story Loop — Step 2 of 6: Preflight approval

      Loop configuration:
      - Story: {{story_path}}
      - Max iterations: {max_iterations}
      - Target branch: {target_branch}
      - Review threshold: {review_threshold} (iterate on any finding, including nits)

      Actions the loop plans to take (category view):

      {{approval_categories}}

      **[a] Approve all** and run autonomously through Steps 3-4
      **[d] Show detailed commands** for each category before deciding
      **[m] Modify** — remove specific categories from approval
      **[c] Cancel** the loop

Story Loop — DONE (converged in {{iteration}} iteration(s))
Pull request opened against `{target_branch}`: {{pr_url}}
Human gate: merge-ready. Review the PR, request changes if needed (which you can feed back by re-running this workflow), or merge.
